<div>
  <h2>The Solution:</h2>
  <p class="big">Six Tournaments, Six Brands.</p>
  <p>
    Collaborating closely with the National Guard, I looked for ways we could
    position the campaign for maximum visibility and success. The key? Treating
    the series not as one ongoing event, but six separate ones.
  </p>
  <div class="side-by-side">
    <div>
      <p class="big">I Want to Break Free</p>
      <p>
        Initially the Guard could only approve assets with a plain white
        background, which restricted our creative potential and visibility. I
        sent them a number of concepts that got them thinking about how a more
        stylish approach could benefit our reach. Convincing the US Army was no
        easy task, but it quickly became a rewarding collaboration and a win-win
        for everyone.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <p class="big">Six-Shooter With a Punch</p>
      <p>
        Employing a unique direction for each of the 2024 year's six
        tournaments, I ensured Code Freedom events would maintain a fresh look
        for each iteration, while maintaining brand cohesion over a series of
        events that spanned influencer showdowns, Apex Legends and CS2 events,
        and top-level competition.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
